# Mapper Extensions

- Implement mappers as extension functions (e.g., `Dto.toDomain()`), not utility classes.
- Keep mapping logic close to source/target models.
- Keep mapper extensions in dedicated files named `*Mapper.kt` (e.g., `UserInfoMapper.kt`).
- Prefer `toDomain()` / `toUi()` / `toData()` naming.

```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD
fun RecipeDto.toDomain(): Recipe = Recipe(
    id = id,
    name = name
)

// ❌ BAD
object RecipeMapper {
    fun toDomain(dto: RecipeDto): Recipe = Recipe(
        id = dto.id,
        name = dto.name
    )
}
```
